01:36.664 --> 01:37.927
(Marion gasps)

01:38.032 --> 01:40.797
Well, how much time
has he got left?

01:40.901 --> 01:42.801
Uh... before the operation?

01:42.903 --> 01:44.598
Mr. Cunningham,
there's no more time.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.537
He's got to go
into the hospital tomorrow.

01:46.640 --> 01:47.801
I hope you understand.

01:47.908 --> 01:49.398
Well, thanks
for coming, Doctor.

01:49.510 --> 01:50.671
I'll see about
getting him a bed.

01:50.778 --> 01:51.870
A bed? Yeah, a bed.

01:51.979 --> 01:53.208
He could use a bed.
Yeah.

01:54.548 --> 01:58.712
Oh, Howard, you're so strong
in a time of crisis.

01:58.819 --> 02:01.652
Well, you get that way in the
hardware business, Marion.

02:06.193 --> 02:07.786
Gee, why so serious?

02:07.895 --> 02:09.419
Yeah, what's
the big deal about a guy

02:09.530 --> 02:10.793
getting his tonsils yanked out?

02:10.898 --> 02:13.060
Shh! He's sleeping.

02:13.167 --> 02:16.102
(hoarsely):
I'm not going to the hospital.

02:16.203 --> 02:18.797
And I'm not
having my tonsils out.

02:18.906 --> 02:20.704
Look, Fonzie, I know
what you're going through.

02:20.808 --> 02:23.743
I had my tonsils removed
just three years ago.

02:23.844 --> 02:26.575
Yeah, those were the two
quietest weeks of my life.

02:26.680 --> 02:30.139
Now, look, this is the third
attack you've had this month.

02:30.250 --> 02:32.548
You have got to go
to the hospital.

02:33.721 --> 02:35.587
Fonz, Joanie and I had

02:35.689 --> 02:37.783
our tonsils taken out years ago.

02:37.891 --> 02:39.859
- Yeah. -My throat's just
starting to feel better.

02:39.960 --> 02:41.086
(laughs)

02:41.195 --> 02:42.663
<i>I'm sorry. I'm sorry.</i>

02:42.763 --> 02:45.824
Just a little sickroom
levity, you know.

02:45.933 --> 02:47.731
Now is not the time to go...

02:47.835 --> 02:49.496
(squeakily):
I can't talk anymore.

02:49.603 --> 02:51.401
Oh, he lost his voice.

02:51.505 --> 02:54.497
Well, that settles it--
he has definitely got to go in.

02:54.608 --> 02:58.044
Howard is right, Arthur.

03:00.314 --> 03:02.612
-"Good night, Mrs. C."
-"Good night, Mrs. C."

03:02.716 --> 03:05.708
-"Mr. C."
-"Good night, Mr. C," yeah.

03:05.819 --> 03:06.843
-"See you, Shortcake."
- Gee.

03:09.056 --> 03:11.047
-(mouths words)
- He says

03:11.158 --> 03:13.889
- He's not going to the hospital.
-he's not going to the hospital.

03:16.130 --> 03:18.098
Oh, yes, you are!

03:19.533 --> 03:21.433
Let's get one thing straight:

03:21.535 --> 03:24.527
The doctor says that you
have to have those tonsils out

03:24.638 --> 03:26.504
and that's exactly
what's gonna happen,

03:26.607 --> 03:28.871
if I have to
take 'em out myself.

03:28.976 --> 03:31.411
Now, you may not
care about yourself,

03:31.512 --> 03:34.140
but we care about you.

03:34.248 --> 03:36.342
So there is no
Halloween party for you.

03:36.450 --> 03:38.145
Tomorrow you go
to the hospital,

03:38.252 --> 03:39.617
and that's final,

03:39.720 --> 03:41.017
<i>finis,</i>

03:41.121 --> 03:42.987
kaputamundo!

03:50.831 --> 03:51.889
WOMAN (over P.A.):
Dr. Curtis. Dr. Curtis.

03:51.999 --> 03:54.434
Well, Fonzie,
this was the only bed available.

03:55.636 --> 03:57.070
Look, it's-it's a cute room.

03:57.171 --> 04:00.072
- Heyyy.
- Oh, yeah, sorry.

04:00.174 --> 04:01.664
Well, look at the
bright side, Fonz.

04:01.775 --> 04:04.472
Your inflammation is down,
your voice is normal.

